# Root .env — app-level environment variables only.
# Supabase local stack configuration lives in supabase/.env (auto-generated by `pnpm setup:env`).
#
# Local dev workflow:
# 1. Run `supabase start`
# 2. Run `pnpm setup:env` — writes apps/api/.env, apps/web/.env, and supabase/.env
#
# Auth emails in local dev are captured by Mailpit — open http://127.0.0.1:54324
# (also printed by `supabase start` / `supabase status`). See README § Local auth emails.
#
# --- apps/api/.env (Nest — Supabase server-side only) ---
# Or manually: `supabase status -o env`
# SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<ANON_KEY from supabase status -o env>
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<SERVICE_ROLE_KEY>
# MEDIA_BUCKET=media
# SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=<JWT_SECRET>
# PORT=3001
# CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
# APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
# PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
#
# --- apps/web/.env ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3001
